<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Ppu pallete and HSV help!!]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10501&amp;p=118163#p118163"><![CDATA[
Bavi_H is correct. NES color is HSL, but not in some paint programs' HSL/HSV color space that's based on following the edges of the RGB cube. It's based on an HSL interpretation of the <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/YUV" class="postlink">YUV color space</a>, where L is Y, and S and H are the polar coordinates of U and V.<br /><br />Until you figure out how to synthesize your own palette, I'd recommend just preloading <a href="http://bisqwit.iki.fi/utils/nespalette.php" class="postlink">Bisqwit's palette</a>.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Sep 16, 2013 9:38 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
